tool.help:
========================================================================= t-distributed stochastic neighborhood embedding (tSNE) (`scanpy.tl.tsne`) =========================================================================
For making TSNE plots, please use `Scanpy PlotEmbed` with the output of this tool and enter "tsne" as the name of the embedding to plot.
t-distributed stochastic neighborhood embedding (tSNE) (Maaten et al, 2008) has been proposed for visualizating single-cell data by (Amir et al, 2013). Here, by default, we use the implementation of *scikit-learn* (Pedregosa et al, 2011).
It yields `X_tsne`, tSNE coordinates of data.
@HELP@
